cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on enriching Chinese word embeddings, which falls under the scope of cs.CL.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed Dual-channel Word Embedding (DWE) model involves joint learning of sequential and spatial information of characters, which is a machine learning task.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of morphological information to enrich word embeddings is a common technique in natural language processing and falls under the scope of AI.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The proposed DWE model involves the use of neural networks to learn the joint representation of stroke and glyph information, which falls under the scope of cs.NE.
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The use of glyph information in Chinese characters involves analyzing the spatial arrangement of strokes, which is similar to computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV is also a possible sub-category.
